---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Privacy"
  description="StackCompass privacy notice: what minimal analytics we may collect, what we don't collect, and how to opt out."
  activeNav=""
  showDisclosure={false}
  slug="/privacy/"
  ogType="website"
>
  <h1>Privacy Notice</h1>
  <p style="color:#52606d;font-size:0.9rem;">Last updated: 2026-07-22</p>

  <div class="lede">
    <p>StackCompass is a small, US-based affiliate comparison site. This notice explains, in plain language, what little data this site may collect and why. It is written for a US-first audience; if you're visiting from elsewhere, the same practices apply unless noted.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>What we may collect</h2>
  <p>If basic web analytics are enabled on this site, they may record aggregate, non-identifying information such as:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Which pages were viewed and roughly how long a page was open</li>
    <li>General device/browser type and approximate (city/region-level, not precise) location inferred from IP address</li>
    <li>Which internal link or button was clicked, including <code>/go/</code> affiliate links, so we can tell which recommendations are useful</li>
    <li>Referring site or search term that led to a page, where available</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What we do not collect</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>No account creation, login, or user profiles</li>
    <li>No payment or financial information — we never process a purchase; sign-ups happen on the vendor's own site</li>
    <li>No sensitive categories of data (health, financial account numbers, government ID numbers, precise geolocation, biometric data)</li>
    <li>No sale of personal information to third parties</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Cookies and local storage</h2>
  <p>If analytics are active, they may use standard, first- or third-party analytics cookies to distinguish repeat visits in aggregate. The <a href="/tools/which-tool-fits-me/">recommender quiz</a> on this site does not use cookies, <code>localStorage</code>, or <code>sessionStorage</code> — your answers exist only in the page's memory while it's open and are discarded when you leave or reload.</p>

  <h2>Affiliate links</h2>
  <p>Outbound links to marketing-tool vendors are internal <code>/go/&lt;program&gt;/</code> pages that may pass you to that vendor's own affiliate-tracking link. Once you leave this site, the vendor's own privacy policy governs any data they collect. See our <a href="/disclosure/">disclosure</a> page for how affiliate links work here.</p>

  <h2>Your choices / opt-out</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>You can use standard browser settings (cookie blocking, "Do Not Track," tracking-protection extensions) to limit analytics collection on this site.</li>
    <li>If a specific analytics opt-out link is offered by our analytics provider, it will be linked here: <span class="todo">analytics opt-out link — add before publish</span>.</li>
    <li>To ask what data (if any) we hold about you, or to request deletion, contact: <span class="todo">privacy contact address — add before publish</span>.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Changes to this notice</h2>
  <p>If this notice changes materially, we'll update the "Last updated" date above.</p>

  <p><a href="/disclosure/">← Back to Disclosure</a></p>
</Layout>
